A '''glass breaker''' is a small hand tool designed to aid in the emergency [[Vehicle extrication|extrication]] of occupants from a vehicle. Most glass breakers contain a sharp pointed metal tip for breaking [[Toughened glass|tempered glass]] and a sharp [[knife]] for slicing through [[Seat belt|seatbelts]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hayspost.com/2017/04/26/at-least-5-children-have-died-so-far-this-year-from-heatstroke-inside-vehicles/|title=At least 5 children have died so far this year from heatstroke inside vehicles|date=2017-04-26|website=Hays Post|access-date=2017-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/affordable-car-gadgets-improve-driving-2017-5/#gps-tracker-8|title=13 must-have car gadgets that cost less than $100|work=Business Insider|access-date=2017-05-24|language=en}}</ref> Glass breakers are also built into other tools, such as [[flashlight]]s or [[Multi-tool|multitools]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.treehugger.com/gadgets/elumen-solar-led-flashlight-great-addition-your-glovebox-emergency-kit-review.html|title=E.LUMEN solar LED flashlight is a great addition to your glovebox & emergency kit (Review)|work=TreeHugger|access-date=2017-05-24}}</ref> Unlike [[Emergency hammer|bus mallets]], glass breakers are smaller and generally [[Private property|privately owned]].

