{{refimprove|date=September 2008}}
The '''Illinois Section American Water Works Association (ISAWWA)''' is part of the national [[American Water Works Association]]. Established in 1909, the ISAWWA currently represents over 1770 [[Public water supply|public water supplies]] of all sizes. ISAWWA members are administrators, utility operators, professional [[engineer]]s, [[General contractor|contractor]]s, manufacturers, [[scientist]]s, [[professor]]s, [[health professional]]s, [[regulatory agency|regulators]], and ordinary citizens.
The mission of ISAWWA is the advancement and dissemination of knowledge concerning the practices in the design, construction, operation, and management of [[water purification|water works]], and the promotion of [[public health]], [[public safety|safety]], and welfare.
