'''Planar Crown''' is a series of [[Blind mate connector|Blind mate]] electrical RF connectors manufactured by API Weinchel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.microwavejournal.com/articles/14783-planar-crown-universal-connector-system|title=PLANAR CROWN® Universal Connector System|access-date=2018-07-31|language=en}}</ref><ref>http://weinschel.apitech.com/weinschel/pdfiles/WMOD_7004A-7005A.pdf</ref> It is fitted for example to the [[RF connector|RF input connector]] of the [[Tektronix]] Real Time Spectrum Analyzer RTSA-5000 series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tek.com/datasheet/spectrum-analyzers-datasheet|title=Spectrum Analyzers Datasheet  RSA5000 Series {{!}} Tektronix|last=|first=|date=|website=www.tek.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-07-31}}</ref> An adapter is required to connect the more common [[N connector|N-type]] or 3.5 mm connectors.

